      Oops
   =20
 =20
You wouldn=E2=80=99t know it from a quick look at Bloomberg, but the stock =
of AeroCentury Corp. closed at $47.99 on Friday. Then over the weekend it c=
ompleted a 5-for-1 stock split, so Bloomberg=E2=80=99s historical price pag=
e retroactively adjusted to show a Friday closing price of $9.598. Then peo=
ple woke up for pre-market trading this morning and =E2=80=A6=C2=A0uh =E2=
=80=A6NYSE Arca Equities in conjunction with other UTP exchanges, have rule=
d to bust all erroneous trades in ACY - AeroCentury Corp, executed between =
4:00:00 - 4:04:00 ET today, at or above $11.52. This ruling is not eligible=
 for appeal.Basically what seems to have happened=C2=A0here is you have a c=
omputer program to buy and sell AeroCentury stock, and the program merrily =
goes along and closes Friday thinking that AeroCentury is trading at $47.99=
, and then based on that and developments over the weekend it thinks =E2=80=
=9CI will buy AeroCentury at $47=C2=A0or sell it at $49=E2=80=9D or whateve=
r (actual numbers not important), and then before Monday morning you either=
 do or do not update the program to be like =E2=80=9Cdon=E2=80=99t forget t=
o divide everything by 5.=E2=80=9D And some people do and some people don=
=E2=80=99t. And the people who don=E2=80=99t, their programs wake up at 4 a=
.m. with a $47.00 / $49.00 market for AeroCentury, and the people who do, t=
heir programs wake up at 4 a.m. on Monday with a a $9.40 / $9.80 market for=
 AeroCentury, and the people who think about it for a moment longer wake up=
 with a $9.40 / $45.00 market for AeroCentury and sell some stock to the pe=
ople who forgot at comically inflated prices. And then the stock exchanges =
bust the trades because this stuff =E2=80=94=C2=A0setting up to profit from=
 other people=E2=80=99s ignorance and fat fingers =E2=80=94=C2=A0is really =
 more of a crypto thing.
